verbs.description: bedung (third-person singular simple present bedungs, present participle bedunging, simple past and past participle bedunged)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To cover with dung or manure.
(transitive, sometimes figuratively) To bedaub or defile.
examples: […]  had not God's inexpected champion, by divine instinct, taken up the monster, and vanquished him; leaving all but his head to bedung that earth, which had lately shaken at his terror.
